<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1900,2035]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,933]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">
Given the variation in external morphology as previously noted, a final pair of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1937" box="[1039,1193,1900,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1193,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Strigivenifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with almost identical male genitalia described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V." box="[466,818,1936,1962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" pagination="904 - 919" refId="ref6695" refString="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V. (2013) A review of the genus Strigivenifera Hering, 1937 (Lepidoptera, Chrysopolomidae) with a description of ten new species. Entomological Review, 93 (7), 904 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873813070142" type="journal article" year="2013">Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin (2013)</bibRefCitation>
is addressed here: 
<taxonomicName authority="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin, 2013" authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[1032,1152,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">S. bartschi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V." pageId="8" pageNumber="59" pagination="904 - 919" refId="ref6695" refString="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V. (2013) A review of the genus Strigivenifera Hering, 1937 (Lepidoptera, Chrysopolomidae) with a description of ten new species. Entomological Review, 93 (7), 904 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873813070142" type="journal article" year="2013">Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(TL: 
<collectingCountry box="[272,347,1972,1998]" name="Kenya" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">Kenya</collectingCountry>
) and 
<emphasis box="[408,546,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V." box="[553,891,1972,1998]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" pagination="904 - 919" refId="ref6695" refString="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V. (2013) A review of the genus Strigivenifera Hering, 1937 (Lepidoptera, Chrysopolomidae) with a description of ten new species. Entomological Review, 93 (7), 904 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873813070142" type="journal article" year="2013">Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin, 2013</bibRefCitation>
(TL: 
<collectingCountry box="[956,1017,1972,1998]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">DRC</collectingCountry>
; note the 
<typeStatus box="[1123,1221,1972,1998]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">holotype</typeStatus>
locality on the distribution map of 
<emphasis box="[338,475,2008,2034]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
is incorrect). When considering just the adult morphology of the illustrated 
<typeStatus box="[1320,1432,2008,2034]" pageId="8" pageNumber="59">holotypes</typeStatus>
, the difference between these two species is clear as 
<emphasis box="[725,863,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
is considerably darker than the related species with more intensive colouration. However, as outlined previously, the absence of further illustrations of each species makes it difficult to understand the level of intraspecific variation, as was found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[1069,1225,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albidiscalis">
<emphasis box="[1069,1225,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. albidiscalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The striking similarities in the male genitalia are as follows: the juxta processes are extremely long and thin, the valve is wide and gradually tapers, there is a complete lack of cornuti, and the distinct aedeagus possesses two moderately sclerotised projections at the distal end. This final characteristic is perhaps the most diagnostic, as in all other 
<taxonomicName pageId="9" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[1282,1436,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Strigivenifera</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
the distal portion of the aedeagus is membranous and very weakly sclerotised. Unfortunately, the differential diagnoses provided by the authors lack details and only briefly compares the external morphology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[1315,1436,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. bartschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[208,364,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albidiscalis">
<emphasis box="[208,364,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. albidiscalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[378,450,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. oris</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[463,530,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. neo</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V." box="[537,875,439,465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" pagination="904 - 919" refId="ref6695" refString="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V. (2013) A review of the genus Strigivenifera Hering, 1937 (Lepidoptera, Chrysopolomidae) with a description of ten new species. Entomological Review, 93 (7), 904 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873813070142" type="journal article" year="2013">Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin, 2013</bibRefCitation>
and 
<emphasis box="[929,1067,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
, whilst 
<emphasis box="[1156,1293,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
is compared only with 
<emphasis box="[265,338,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. oris</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[392,461,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. neo</emphasis>
; it should be noted that neither 
<emphasis box="[818,891,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. oris</emphasis>
nor 
<emphasis box="[942,1011,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. neo</emphasis>
occur in sympatry with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[1286,1406,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[1286,1406,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. bartschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis box="[151,289,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
. The comparison of the near-identical genital morphology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[981,1101,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[981,1101,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. bartschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1155,1293,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
was surprisingly neglected by the authors.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">
The only noticeable difference between the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[885,1005,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[885,1005,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. bartschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1060,1198,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
is in the shape of the ventral edge of the valve: in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[479,600,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[479,600,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. bartschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this edge is slightly more truncate whilst it is more rounded in the allied species. In order to investigate whether this was mere variation, two barcode-confirmed specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1306,1432,655,681]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Nord-Kivu" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Nord-Kivu</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,209,691,717]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">DRC</collectingCountry>
were dissected (BOLD process ids./gen. slide Nos.: ANLMN7890-21/TT 125; ANLMN7892-21/TT 124) and compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[301,423,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[301,423,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. bartschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the type locality (BOLD process ids.: LIMBC814-11–LIMBC816-11; LIMBC818- 11). The results showed an intermediate valve shape between both species (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1148,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1690,1714]" captionTargetBox="[279,1308,189,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[268,1319,179,1664]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Adult male Strigivenifera (deposited at ANHRT unless otherwise stated). 1. S. albidiscalis, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8462-21/TT 118); 2. S. albidiscalis, Zambia (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8454- 21/TT 111); 3. S. albidiscalis, Zambia (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8460-21/TT 112); 4. S. eborea, Ivory Coast (BOLD process id./gen. slide No. ANLMN8471-21/TT 114); 5. S. eborea, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8472/TT 115); 6. S. eborea, Ivory Coast (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8466-21/TT 123); 7. S. eborea, Ivory Coast (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8465-21/TT 141); 8. S. smithi sp. n., HT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8475-21/TT 122); 9. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: AN- LMN8474/TT 121), 10. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (gen. slide No.: TT 139); 11. S. bartschi (PT of S. tatooifera), DRC (gen. slide No.: CHRY-11-52) (RMCA); 12. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7892-21/TT 124); 13. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7890-21/TT 125)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876376/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Figs. 12–13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1161,1235,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1532,1556]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,193,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-27@6.[151,1436,181,1508]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Male genitalia of Strigivenifera (a. clasping apparatus; b. aedeagus). 21. S. smithi sp. n., HT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.:ANLMN8475-21/TT 122); 22. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8474/TT 121), 23. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (gen. slide No.: TT 139); 24. S. bartschi (PT of S. tatooifera), DRC (gen. slide No.: CHRY-11-52) (RMCA); 25. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7892-21/TT 124); 26. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7890-21/TT 125)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876380/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">25–26</figureCitation>
), as also found in a 
<typeStatus box="[171,267,799,825]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[307,445,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[462,555,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1690,1714]" captionTargetBox="[279,1308,189,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[268,1319,179,1664]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. Adult male Strigivenifera (deposited at ANHRT unless otherwise stated). 1. S. albidiscalis, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8462-21/TT 118); 2. S. albidiscalis, Zambia (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8454- 21/TT 111); 3. S. albidiscalis, Zambia (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8460-21/TT 112); 4. S. eborea, Ivory Coast (BOLD process id./gen. slide No. ANLMN8471-21/TT 114); 5. S. eborea, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8472/TT 115); 6. S. eborea, Ivory Coast (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8466-21/TT 123); 7. S. eborea, Ivory Coast (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8465-21/TT 141); 8. S. smithi sp. n., HT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8475-21/TT 122); 9. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: AN- LMN8474/TT 121), 10. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (gen. slide No.: TT 139); 11. S. bartschi (PT of S. tatooifera), DRC (gen. slide No.: CHRY-11-52) (RMCA); 12. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7892-21/TT 124); 13. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7890-21/TT 125)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876376/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">Figs. 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[567,598,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1532,1556]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,193,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-27@6.[151,1436,181,1508]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Male genitalia of Strigivenifera (a. clasping apparatus; b. aedeagus). 21. S. smithi sp. n., HT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.:ANLMN8475-21/TT 122); 22. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN8474/TT 121), 23. S. smithi sp. n., PT, Sierra Leone (gen. slide No.: TT 139); 24. S. bartschi (PT of S. tatooifera), DRC (gen. slide No.: CHRY-11-52) (RMCA); 25. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7892-21/TT 124); 26. S. bartschi, DRC (BOLD process id./gen. slide No.: ANLMN7890-21/TT 125)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876380/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">24</figureCitation>
), while every other feature of the entire male genitalia remained identical. Furthermore, the APWD between the 
<collectingCountry box="[575,633,835,861]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">DRC</collectingCountry>
and Kenyan specimens was just 0.9%. From this, it is herein concluded that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin" authorityYear="2013" box="[201,321,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Strigivenifera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bartschi">
<emphasis box="[201,321,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. bartschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[376,514,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
are synonymous and the latter is synonymised with the former: 
<emphasis box="[1238,1376,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">S. tatooifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V." pageId="9" pageNumber="60" pagination="904 - 919" refId="ref6695" refString="Kurshakov, P. A. &amp; Zolotuhin, V. V. (2013) A review of the genus Strigivenifera Hering, 1937 (Lepidoptera, Chrysopolomidae) with a description of ten new species. Entomological Review, 93 (7), 904 - 919. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873813070142" type="journal article" year="2013">Kurshakov &amp; Zolotuhin, 2013</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[454,531,907,933]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60">syn. n.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
